yerZero/CoreRouter.sol:121","LayerZero/CoreRouter.sol:124"],"claim":"`redeem()` computes `expectedUnderlying` using `exchangeRateStored()` before calling `LErc20.redeem(_amount)`. `redeem` can accrue interest and realize a higher exchange rate, but the router transfers only the stale lower `expectedUnderlying` amount.","impact":"Redeemers can be consistently underpaid while surplus underlying remains trapped in router balances, creating direct user fund loss and accounting drift.","paths":["User calls `redeem(_amount, _lToken)` after accrual gap","Router snapshots stale exchange rate and computes `expectedUnderlying`","`LErc20.redeem` accrues and credits higher underlying to router","Router transfers only stale amount to user"],"round":6,"source_agents":["codex_1"]},{"id":"F-022","severity":"Medium","confidence":"high","title":"Liquidation credits seized collateral without registering liquidator supplied-asset membership","locations":["LayerZero/CoreRouter.sol:310","LayerZero/CoreRouter.sol:313","LayerZero/CrossChainRouter.sol:337","LayerZero/CrossChainRouter.sol:340"],"claim":"Same-chain and cross-chain liquidation paths increase liquidator `totalInvestment` for seized collateral but do not call `addUserSuppliedAsset(liquidator, lTokenCollateral)`. Liquidity logic iterates `userSuppliedAssets`, so these seized positions can be invisible to collateral accounting.","impact":"Liquidators may be unable to redeem seized collateral or may face distorted liquidity checks unless they had already registered that market, weakening liquidation usability and incentives.","paths":["Liquidation seizes collateral and only updates `totalInvestment` for liquidator","`userSuppliedAssets` is not updated for the seized market","Subsequent `redeem`/liquidity checks omit seized market collateral for that liquidator"],"round":6,"source_agents":["codex_1","opencode_1"]},{"id":"F-023","severity":"Medium","confidence":"high","title":"Cross-chain liquidation can send unexecutable seize amount and revert on collateral-chain execution","locations":["LayerZero/CrossChainRouter.sol:268","LayerZero/CrossChainRouter.sol:274","LayerZero/CrossChainRouter.sol:333"],"claim":"`_executeLiquidationCore` forwards computed `seizeTokens` without bounding against borrower collateral on source chain. `_handleLiquidationExecute` then subtracts `payload.amount` from borrower `totalInvestment`; if `seizeTokens` exceeds balance, subtraction underflows and reverts.","impact":"Cross-chain liquidation messages can become revert-only, blocking liquidation completion and creating retry/stuck-message DoS behavior for unhealthy positions.","paths":["Liquidator initiates cross-chain liquidation with repay that maps to large `seizeTokens`","Router sends `CrossChainLiquidationExecute` with `payload.amount = seizeTokens`","Collateral-chain handler subtracts `payload.amount` from borrower collateral and reverts on underflow"],"round":6,"source_agents":["codex_1","opencode_1"]},{"id":"F-024","severity":"Medium","confidence":"low","title":"Unbounded per-user asset-set iteration can gas-DoS risk checks and liquidation paths","locations":["LayerZero/LendStorage.sol:170","LayerZero/LendStorage.sol:180","LayerZero/LendStorage.sol:394","LayerZero/LendStorage.sol:421"],"claim":"`userSuppliedAssets` and `userBorrowedAssets` have no enforced upper bound, while `getHypotheticalAccountLiquidityCollateral` iterates both sets with multiple external calls per item. Large user asset sets can push borrow/redeem/liquidation checks beyond practical gas limits.","impact":"Highly fragmented positions can become difficult or impossible to process, potentially preventing timely liquidation and increasing bad-debt risk for affected accounts.","paths":["User accumulates many supplied/borrowed markets","Any operation requiring liquidity checks calls `getHypotheticalAccountLiquidityCollateral`","Looped per-asset pricing/exchange-rate work exceeds gas budget and reverts"],"round":6,"source_agents":["opencode_1","merge_layer"]},{"id":"F-025","severity":"High","confidence":"high","title":"Cross-chain debt accrual uses local-chain borrow index instead of debt-chain index","locations":["LayerZero/LendStorage.sol:491","LayerZero/LendStorage.sol:499","LayerZero/CrossChainRouter.sol:722"],"claim":"Cross-chain borrow records persist `borrowIndex` captured from the remote debt market, but `borrowWithInterest` accrues those records with `LTokenInterface(_lToken).borrowIndex()` from the local-chain lToken passed by local accounting loops. For cross-chain borrows this can be a different market/index domain.","impact":"When the two chains’ borrow indices diverge, cross-chain liabilities are mispriced in risk checks. Under-accrual can allow excess borrowing/redeeming and create bad debt; over-accrual can cause unfair liquidations/DoS.","paths":["Source-chain `ValidBorrowRequest` stores `payload.borrowIndex` from destination debt market in `crossChainBorrows`.","Later, source-chain liquidity checks call `borrowWithInterest(account, localLToken)` via `getHypotheticalAccountLiquidityCollateral`.","`borrowWithInterest` multiplies by local `borrowIndex()` instead of the debt-chain market index basis of the stored record.","Computed debt deviates from true remote debt, breaking collateralization decisions."],"round":7,"source_agents":["codex_1","merge_layer"]},{"id":"F-026","severity":"Medium","confidence":"high","title":"Liquidation close-factor cap uses stale principal instead of accrued debt","locations":["LayerZero/CoreRouter.sol:341","LayerZero/CoreRouter.sol:353","LayerZero/CoreRouter.sol:354"],"claim":"In `liquidateBorrowAllowedInternal`, the maximum repay (`maxClose`) is computed from `borrowBalance.amount` (stored principal snapshot) rather than the borrower’s current accrued debt amount used for solvency evaluation.","impact":"After interest accrual, liquidation can be artificially capped below intended close-factor of actual debt, slowing deleveraging and increasing residual bad-debt risk for unhealthy accounts.","paths":["Borrow accrues interest so real debt grows above stored principal.","Liquidator calls same-chain liquidation.","Function computes `maxClose = closeFactor * borrowBalance.amount` (stale principal), not closeFactor times current debt.","Allowed repay can be materially too low, requiring extra transactions and delaying risk reduction."],"round":7,"source_agents":["codex_1","merge_layer"]}],"rejected_candidates":[{"title":"Cross-chain borrow lacks source chain verification allowing stale collateral use","source_agents":["opencode_1"],"reason":"Duplicate of existing F-002 (same stale collateral snapshot/TOCTOU root cause and exploit path)."},{"title":"LEND reward claim allows permissionless claim for any address array","source_agents":["opencode_1"],"reason":"Not reportable as fund-theft: claims are transferred to the specified holders, not caller; this is generally permissionless-claim behavior and does not add material harm beyond existing F-014."},{"title":"Cross-chain repay uses wrong chain identifier for same-chain storage","source_agents":["opencode_1"],"reason":"Substantially overlaps existing F-003/F-017 accounting flaws; no distinct new root cause established."},{"title":"Cross-chain liquidation failure sends tokens without balance verification","source_agents":["opencode_1"],"reason":"Already captured by F-019 (refund without escrow / failure-path payout mismatch)."},{"title":"Cross-chain repay validates only srcEid without verifying borrow position exists on that chain","source_agents":["opencode_1"],"reason":"Duplicate of existing F-012 (repay lookup keyed only by `srcEid`, ambiguous position selection)."},{"title":"No access control on authorizedContracts - any authorized caller can modify any user state","source_agents":["opencode_1"],"reason":"Trust-model observation, not a protocol bug by itself; privileged authorized contracts are expected to mutate user state."},{"title":"Oracle price of zero creates fail-open l