ero/CoreRouter.sol:87"],"claim":"`supply` computes credited lTokens from `exchangeRateStored()` before calling `mint()`. Since `mint()` can accrue interest and mint at a higher exchange rate, internal `mintTokens` credit can exceed actual lTokens received.","impact":"Users can be credited with more internal investment than the protocol actually minted, enabling value extraction at others’ expense and potential insolvency.","paths":["supply -> read exchangeRateStored (stale) -> mint accrues interest/updates rate -> actual minted lTokens < internal mintTokens -> inflated totalInvestment"],"round":2,"source_agents":["codex_1"]},{"id":"F-009","severity":"Medium","confidence":"high","title":"Same-chain liquidation shortfall check re-applies index growth to already-accrued borrow value","locations":["LayerZero/CoreRouter.sol:238","LayerZero/CoreRouter.sol:347","LayerZero/CoreRouter.sol:350"],"claim":"`liquidateBorrow` passes `borrowed` from `getHypotheticalAccountLiquidityCollateral`, which already includes accrued borrow effects; `liquidateBorrowAllowedInternal` multiplies by `currentBorrowIndex / storedBorrowIndex` again, overstating debt in the shortfall test.","impact":"Accounts can be treated as undercollateralized earlier than intended, enabling premature/unfair liquidation.","paths":["liquidateBorrow -> getHypotheticalAccountLiquidityCollateral returns borrowed/collateral","liquidateBorrowAllowedInternal computes borrowedAmount = borrowed * currentIndex / borrowBalance.borrowIndex","borrowedAmount becomes inflated -> `borrowedAmount > collateral` may pass for positions that should not be liquidatable"],"round":2,"source_agents":["codex_1"]},{"id":"F-010","severity":"Medium","confidence":"high","title":"Cross-chain borrow aggregation can hard-revert when both direction records coexist","locations":["LayerZero/LendStorage.sol:83","LayerZero/LendStorage.sol:84","LayerZero/LendStorage.sol:485","LayerZero/CrossChainRouter.sol:641","LayerZero/CrossChainRouter.sol:718"],"claim":"`borrowWithInterest` reverts if both `crossChainBorrows` and `crossChainCollaterals` are non-empty for a user/token. Opposite-direction cross-chain borrowing for the same underlying can populate both arrays on one chain, violating this assumption.","impact":"Borrow/liquidity/liquidation/repay flows that depend on borrow aggregation can revert, creating permissionless DoS and potentially locking user positions.","paths":["Direction A->B borrow creates `crossChainBorrows` on chain A for token X","Direction B->A borrow creates `crossChainCollaterals` on chain A for token X","Any call path invoking borrowWithInterest for that user/token reverts with invariant violation"],"round":2,"source_agents":["codex_1"]},{"id":"F-011","severity":"Medium","confidence":"high","title":"Unchecked ERC20 `transfer` can update protocol state without actual token payout","locations":["LayerZero/CoreRouter.sol:124","LayerZero/CoreRouter.sol:170","LayerZero/CoreRouter.sol:204"],"claim":"Payout paths use raw `IERC20.transfer` and ignore its boolean return value. For non-standard ERC20s that return `false` instead of reverting, execution continues and state changes persist despite failed transfer.","impact":"Users can be debited/indebted without receiving tokens, and protocol accounting can diverge from real token balances.","paths":["redeem/borrow/borrowForCrossChain performs stateful actions and calls raw transfer","token returns false (no revert)","function continues, leaving accounting changed but payout not delivered"],"round":2,"source_agents":["codex_1"]},{"id":"F-012","severity":"Medium","confidence":"medium","title":"Cross-chain repay lookup is ambiguous and keyed only by srcEid","locations":["LayerZero/CrossChainRouter.sol:397","LayerZero/CrossChainRouter.sol:406","LayerZero/CrossChainRouter.sol:539"],"claim":"`_getBorrowDetails` selects a collateral position using only `srcEid` within `crossChainCollaterals[borrower][underlying]`. If multiple positions share the same source chain but differ by other identifiers (e.g., source token), repayment can update the wrong position.","impact":"Repayments can be misattributed, corrupting debt records and impairing liquidation/accounting correctness.","paths":["Borrower has multiple cross-chain collateral records for same borrowed underlying with identical srcEid","repayCrossChainBorrow -> _getBorrowDetails picks first srcEid match","_updateRepaymentState and DestRepay message mutate/propagate wrong position data"],"round":2,"source_agents":["codex_1","opencode_1"]},{"id":"F-013","severity":"High","confidence":"medium","title":"Cross-chain liquidation health check uses seize amount as synthetic new borrow","locations":["LayerZero/CrossChainRouter.sol:273","LayerZero/CrossChainRouter.sol:276","LayerZero/CrossChainRouter.sol:431","LayerZero/CrossChainRouter.sol:433"],"claim":"When validating liquidation on the collateral chain, `_checkLiquidationValid` calls `getHypotheticalAccountLiquidityCollateral` with `borrowAmount = payload.amount`, but `payload.amount` is seizeTokens (collateral quantity), not pending debt. This distorts shortfall evaluation.","impact":"Liquidation eligibility can be misclassified, enabling liquidation of positions that are not actually underwater or causing inconsistent liquidation behavior.","paths":["Chain B computes seizeTokens and sends CrossChainLiquidationExecute with payload.amount = seizeTokens","Chain A _checkLiquidationValid treats payload.amount as hypothetical additional borrow","Borrowed-vs-collateral comparison is based on a wrong variable and can return true for otherwise healthy accounts"],"round":2,"source_agents":["merge_layer","opencode_1"]},{"id":"F-014","severity":"High","confidence":"high","title":"LEND rewards can be claimed repeatedly because accrued balances are never decremented","locations":["LayerZero/CoreRouter.sol:399","LayerZero/CoreRouter.sol:402","LayerZero/CoreRouter.sol:416","LayerZero/LendStorage.sol:76"],"claim":"`claimLend` reads `lendStorage.lendAccrued(holder)` and transfers that amount via `grantLendInternal`, but never writes back a reduced accrued value. The same accrued balance remains claimable on repeated calls.","impact":"Any account with non-zero accrued rewards can repeatedly claim and drain LEND held by the router, including rewards attributable to other users.","paths":["User accrues positive `lendAccrued` once","User calls `claimLend` and receives full accrued amount","`lendAccrued[user]` is unchanged","User repeats claims until router LEND balance is exhausted"],"round":3,"source_agents":["codex_1"]},{"id":"F-015","severity":"High","confidence":"medium","title":"Liquidity checks accept zero oracle prices, creating fail-open borrow authorization","locations":["LayerZero/LendStorage.sol:431","LayerZero/LendStorage.sol:445","LayerZero/LendStorage.sol:460","LayerZero/CoreRouter.sol:152","LayerZero/CrossChainRouter.sol:617"],"claim":"`getHypotheticalAccountLiquidityCollateral` uses oracle prices without validating `price > 0`. If a market price returns `0`, borrow-side effects for that asset become `0`, and collateral checks can pass despite real economic risk.","impact":"During oracle outages/misconfiguration returning zero, users can borrow assets with effectively no borrow value added in checks, potentially extracting pool liquidity and creating bad debt.","paths":["Oracle returns 0 price for borrow market","User calls same-chain or cross-chain borrow","Borrow value contribution is computed as zero in liquidity check","Borrow proceeds while true collateralization is insufficient"],"round":3,"source_agents":["codex_1","opencode_1"]},{"id":"F-016","severity":"Medium","confidence":"low","title":"Borrow/redeem update accounting after external calls, leaving reentrancy window for callback-capable tokens","locations":["LayerZero/CoreRouter.sol:121","LayerZero/CoreRouter.sol:124","LayerZero/CoreRouter.sol:127","LayerZero/CoreRouter.sol:167","LayerZero/CoreRouter.sol:170","LayerZero/CoreRouter.sol:179"],"claim":"`redeem` and `borrow` perform external protocol/token calls before updating internal accounting (`totalInvestment`, `borrowBalance`), and no reentrancy guard exists. Callback-capable listed tokens can reenter while state is stale.","impact":"If a callback-capable market token is listed, an attacker contract may chain nested operations against stale balances to over-redeem/over-borrow relative to intended single-call limits.","paths":["Attacker triggers `borrow` or `redeem` via contract","External token/protocol call executes before accounting update","Callback reenters router and passes checks using stale state","Nested operations extract excess value"],"round":3,"source_agents":["codex_1"]},{"id":"F-017","severity":"High","confidence":"high","title":"Cross-chain repay path incorrectly mutates same-chain borrow storage","locations":["LayerZero/CoreRouter.sol:472","LayerZero/CoreRouter.sol:475","LayerZero/CoreRouter.sol:492","LayerZero/CoreRouter.sol:497","LayerZero/CrossChainRouter.sol:425"],"claim":"Cross-chain repay flows call `CoreRouter.repayBorrowInternal(..., _isSameChain=false)`, but the function always writes to same-chain `borrowBalance` (`removeBorrowBalance`/`updateBorrowBalance`) after repayment. This mixes cross-chain repayment results into same-chain debt storage.","impact":"Debt accounting becomes inconsistent: liabilities can be double-counted (same-chain + cross-chain) causing false shortfall/DoS/unfair liquidation, and full cross-chain repay can erase same-chain borrow records for the same market if present.","paths":["repayCrossChainBorrowInternal -> _handleRepayment -> CoreRouter.repayCrossChainLiquidation","CoreRouter.repayBorrowInternal computes borrowedAmount from cross-chain path (`borrowWithInterest`)","function still updates/removes `borrowBalance[borrower][_lToken]` (same-chain slot)","Cross-chain state is also updated in `_updateRepaymentState`, creating divergent or duplicated debt state"],"round":4,"source_agents":["codex_1"]},{"id":"F-018","severity":"High","confidence":"high","title":"Cross-chain liquidation uses seized-collateral quantity as debt repayment amount","locations":["LayerZero/CrossChainRouter.sol:274","LayerZero/CrossChainRouter.sol:276","LayerZero/CrossChainRouter.sol:355","LayerZero/CrossChainRouter.sol:464","LayerZero/CrossChainRouter.sol:467"],"claim":"`_executeLiquidationCore` encodes `payload.amount = seizeTokens` for `CrossChainLiquidationExecute`. The same `payload.amount` is forwarded in `LiquidationSuccess` and later used by `_handleLiquidationSuccess` as the repay amount (`repayCrossChainBorrowInternal(..., payload.amount, ...)`).","impact":"Debt repayment diverges from intended `repayAmount`: liquidators can seize collateral priced for one value while paying a different debt amount, leaving residual bad debt or extracting value depending on price/exchange-rate relationships.","paths":["Chain B: liquidateCrossChain(repayAmount)","_executeLiquidationCore computes `seizeTokens` and sends as payload.amount","Chain A seizes collateral and returns LiquidationSuccess with same payload.amount","Chain B `_handleLiquidationSuccess` treats payload.amount as debt repay amount"],"round":4,"source_agents":["codex_1"]},{"id":"F-019","severity":"Medium","confidence":"low","title":"Liquidation-failure refund attempts token payout without prior escrow","locations":["LayerZero/CrossChainRouter.sol:172","LayerZero/CrossChainRouter.sol:274","LayerZero/CrossChainRouter.sol:491","LayerZero/CrossChainRouter.sol:478","LayerZero/CrossChainRouter.sol:482"],"claim":"`liquidateCrossChain` does not escrow repay tokens up front, yet failure handling performs `safeTransfer(payload.amount)` to the liquidator in `_handleLiquidationFailure`. The refund amount originates from computed `seizeTokens`, not deposited funds.","impact":"If the token lookup resolves and router holds balance, attackers can trigger failing liquidations and drain router-held tokens without having prepaid; otherwise this contributes to stuck/failing failure-handling messages.","paths":["Attacker calls `liquidateCrossChain` (no token transfer from liquidator)","Cross-chain execution reaches failure branch and sends `LiquidationFailure`","Destination `_handleLiquidationFailure` transfers `payload.amount` to liquidator from router balance"],"round":4,"source_agents":["codex_1"]},{"id":"F-020","severity":"High","confidence":"high","title":"Borrowed-asset tracking can be cleared while debt still exists, hiding liabilities from liquidity checks","locations":["LayerZero/CoreRouter.sol:495","LayerZero/CrossChainRouter.sol:521","LayerZero/CrossChainRouter.sol:560","LayerZero/LendStorage.sol:395","LayerZero/LendStorage.sol:421"],"claim":"Repayment paths remove `userBorrowedAssets` membership for an lToken based on a single ledger becoming empty, without verifying all debt ledgers for that asset are zero. Since liquidity checks iterate only `userBorrowedAssets`, remaining same-chain or cross-chain debt can be omitted from borrow/withdraw risk checks.","impact":"A borrower can retain real debt that is no longer counted in `getHypotheticalAccountLiquidityCollateral`, enabling excess borrowing or redemption and creating bad debt/insolvency risk.","paths":["User has same-chain and cross-chain debt for lToken X -> fully repays same-chain debt -> `CoreRouter.repayBorrowInternal` removes borrowed-asset entry -> cross-chain debt for X is skipped in liquidity loop.","User has same-chain debt and one cross-chain record for lToken X -> full cross-chain repay path (`_updateRepaymentState` or `_handleDestRepayMessage`) removes borrowed-asset entry when that array length is 1 -> same-chain debt remains but is no longer included in liquidity accounting."],"round":5,"source_agents":["codex_1","merge_layer"]},{"id":"F-021","severity":"High","confidence":"high","title":"Redeem pays users using stale pre-accrual exchange rate, causing systematic underpayment","locations":["LayerZero/CoreRouter.sol:115","LayerZero/CoreRouter.sol:121","LayerZero/CoreRouter.sol:124"],"claim":"`redeem()` computes `expectedUnderlying` using `exchangeRateStored()` before calling `LErc20.redeem(_amount)`. `redeem` can accrue interest and realize a higher exchange rate, but the router transfers only the stale lower `expectedUnderlying` amount.","impact":"Redeemers can be consistently underpaid while surplus underlying remains trapped in router balances, creating direct user fund loss and accounting drift.","paths":["User calls `redeem(_amount, _lToken)` after accrual gap","Router snapshots stale exchange rate and computes `expectedUnderlying`","`LErc20.redeem` accrues and credits higher underlying to router","Router transfers only stale amount to user"],"round":6,"source_agents":["codex_1"]},{"id":"F-022","severity":"Medium","confidence":"high","title":"Liquidation credits seized collateral without registering liquidator supplied-asset membership","locations":["LayerZero/CoreRouter.sol:310","LayerZero/CoreRouter.sol:313","LayerZero/CrossChainRouter.sol:337","LayerZero/CrossChainRouter.sol:340"],"claim":"Same-chain and cross-chain liquidation paths increase liquidator `totalInvestment` for seized collateral but do not call `addUserSuppliedAsset(liquidator, lTokenCollateral)`. Liquidity logic iterates `userSuppliedAssets`, so these seized positions can be invisible to collateral accounting.","impact":"Liquidators may be unable to redeem seized collateral or may face distorted liquidity checks unless they had already registered that market, weakening liquidation usability and incentives.","paths":["Liquidation seizes collateral and only updates `totalInvestment` for liquidator","`userSuppliedAssets` is not updated for the seized market","Subsequent `redeem`/liquidity checks omit seized market collateral for that liquidator"],"round":6,"source_agents":["codex_1","opencode_1"]},{"id":"F-023","severity":"Medium","confidence":"high","title":"Cross-chain liquidation can send unexecutable seize amount and revert on collateral-chain execution","locations":["LayerZero/CrossChainRouter.sol:268","LayerZero/CrossChainRouter.sol:274","LayerZero/CrossChainRouter.sol:333"],"claim":"`_executeLiquidationCore` forwards computed `seizeTokens` without bounding against borrower collateral on source chain. `_handleLiquidationExecute` then subtracts `payload.amount` from borrower `totalInvestment`; if `seizeTokens` exceeds balance, subtraction underflows and reverts.","impact":"Cross-chain liquidation messages can become revert-only, blocking liquidation completion and creating retry/stuck-message DoS behavior for unhealthy positions.","paths":["Liquidator initiates cross-chain liquidation with repay that maps to large `seizeTokens`","Router sends `CrossChainLiquidationExecute` with `payload.amount = seizeTokens`","Collateral-chain handler subtracts `payload.amount` from borrower collateral and reverts on underflow"],"round":6,"source_agents":["codex_1","opencode_1"]},{"id":"F-024","severity":"Medium","confidence":"low","title":"Unbounded per-user asset-set iteration can gas-DoS risk checks and liquidation paths","locations":["LayerZero/LendStorage.sol:170","LayerZero/LendStorage.sol:180","LayerZero/LendStorage.sol:394","LayerZero/LendStorage.sol:421"],"claim":"`userSuppliedAssets` and `userBorrowedAssets` have no enforced upper bound, while `getHypotheticalAccountLiquidityCollateral` iterates both sets with multiple external calls per item. Large user asset sets can push borrow/redeem/liquidation checks beyond practical gas limits.","impact":"Highly fragmented positions can become difficult or impossible to process, potentially preventing timely liquidation and increasing bad-debt risk for affected accounts.","paths":["User accumulates many supplied/borrowed markets","Any operation requiring liquidity checks calls `getHypotheticalAccountLiquidityCollateral`","Looped per-asset pricing/exchange-rate work exceeds gas budget and reverts"],"round":6,"source_agents":["opencode_1","merge_layer"]},{"id":"F-025","severity":"High","confidence":"high","title":"Cross-chain debt accrual uses local-chain borrow index instead of debt-chain index","locations":["LayerZero/LendStorage.sol:491","LayerZero/LendStorage.sol:499","LayerZero/CrossChainRouter.sol:722"],"claim":"Cross-chain borrow records persist `borrowIndex` captured from the remote debt market, but `borrowWithInterest` accrues those records with `LTokenInterface(_lToken).borrowIndex()` from the local-chain lToken passed by local accounting loops. For cross-chain borrows this can be a different market/index domain.","impact":"When the two chains’ borrow indices diverge, cross-chain liabilities are mispriced in risk checks. Under-accrual can allow excess borrowing/redeeming and create bad debt; over-accrual can cause unfair liquidations/DoS.","paths":["Source-chain `ValidBorrowRequest` stores `payload.borrowIndex` from destination debt market in `crossChainBorrows`.","Later, source-chain liquidity checks call `borrowWithInterest(account, localLToken)` via `getHypotheticalAccountLiquidityCollateral`.","`borrowWithInterest` multiplies by local `borrowIndex()` instead of the debt-chain market index basis of the stored record.","Computed debt deviates from true remote debt, breaking collateralization decisions."],"round":7,"source_agents":["codex_1","merge_layer"]},{"id":"F-026","severity":"Medium","confidence":"high","title":"Liquidation close-factor cap uses stale principal instead of accrued debt","locations":["LayerZero/CoreRouter.sol:341","LayerZero/CoreRouter.sol:353","LayerZero/CoreRouter.sol:354"],"claim":"In `liquidateBorrowAllowedInternal`, the maximum repay (`maxClose`) is computed from `borrowBalance.amount` (stored principal snapshot) rather than the borrower’s current accrued debt amount used for solvency evaluation.","impact":"After interest accrual, liquidation can be artificially capped below intended close-factor of actual debt, slowing deleveraging and increasing residual bad-debt risk for unhealthy accounts.","paths":["Borrow accrues interest so real debt grows above stored principal.","Liquidator calls same-chain liquidation.","Function computes `maxClose = closeFactor * borrowBalance.amount` (stale principal), not closeFactor times current debt.","Allowed repay can be materially too low, requiring extra transactions and delaying risk reduction."],"round":7,"source_agents":["codex_1","merge_layer"]}],"rejected_candidates":[{"title":"Cross-chain borrow lacks source chain verification allowing stale collateral use","source_agents":["opencode_1"],"reason":"Duplicate of existing F-002 (same stale collateral snapshot/TOCTOU root cause and exploit path)."},{"title":"LEND reward claim allows permissionless claim for any address array","source_agents":["opencode_1"],"reason":"Not reportable as fund-theft: claims are transferred to the specified holders, not caller; this is generally permissionless-claim behavior and does not add material harm beyond existing F-014."},{"title":"Cross-chain repay uses wrong chain identifier for same-chain storage","source_agents":["opencode_1"],"reason":"Substantially overlaps existing F-003/F-017 accounting flaws; no distinct new root cause established."},{"title":"Cross-chain liquidation failure sends tokens without balance verification","source_agents":["opencode_1"],"reason":"Already captured by F-019 (refund without escrow / failure-path payout mismatch)."},{"title":"Cross-chain repay validates only srcEid without verifying borrow position exists on that chain","source_agents":["opencode_1"],"reason":"Duplicate of existing F-012 (repay lookup keyed only by `srcEid`, ambiguous position selection)."},{"title":"No access control on authorizedContracts - any authorized caller can modify any user state","source_agents":["opencode_1"],"reason":"Trust-model observation, not a protocol bug by itself; privileged authorized contracts are expected to mutate user state."},{"title":"Oracle price of zero creates fail-open